        <h2>Key Terms</h2>
        <table class="table table-sm">
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>MVC</strong></td>
                    <td>Model-View-Controller. A design pattern that separates app logic into three components.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Model</strong></td>
                    <td>Data classes that represent the structure of your data (e.g., <code>TodoItem.cs</code>).</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>View</strong></td>
                    <td>The UI layer. Razor templates (<code>.cshtml</code>) that render HTML to the browser.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Controller</strong></td>
                    <td>Handles HTTP requests, processes data, and returns Views. The middleman between Model and View.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Razor</strong></td>
                    <td>A syntax for embedding C# code in HTML using <code>@@</code> symbols.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>SDK</strong></td>
                    <td>Software Development Kit. Includes the compiler, libraries, and CLI tools.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>CLI</strong></td>
                    <td>Command Line Interface. Run commands like <code>dotnet run</code> in the terminal.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>NuGet</strong></td>
                    <td>Package manager for .NET. Like npm for Node.js.</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

