        <h2>Creating the Project</h2>
        <p>Create a new ASP.NET Core MVC project:</p>
        <pre><code class="language-bash">dotnet new mvc -n TodoApp
cd TodoApp
dotnet run</code></pre>
        <p>
            Navigate to <code>https://localhost:5001</code> to see the default template.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4">

        <h2>Hot Reload with dotnet watch</h2>
        <p>
            Use <code>dotnet watch run</code> to automatically reload the app when you make changes.
            This is useful during development so you don't have to restart the server manually.
        </p>
        <pre><code class="language-bash">dotnet watch run</code></pre>
        <p>
            The watcher will detect changes to <code>.cs</code>, <code>.cshtml</code>, and other files,
            then automatically rebuild and refresh your browser.
        </p>
        <p>To stop the watcher, press <code>Ctrl+C</code> in the terminal.</p>

